{
  "doc_id": "13893",
  "text": "Biomphalaria pfeifferi used in Illumina sequencing were collected from Kasabong stream in Asembo Village, Nyanza Province, western Kenya (34.42037°E, 0.15869°S) and transferred to our field lab at The Centre for Global Health Research (CGHR) at Kisian, western Kenya. Snails sized 6-9mm in shell diameter were placed under natural light to check for shedding of digenetic trematode cercariae [CITATION_1] . Snails shedding only S. mansoni cercariae and non-shedding controls were used in this study. More details of collections and processing can be found in Buddenborg et al. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
